    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 4,
        "summary": "Keep the commandments and live\u2014With all your getting, get understanding\u2014Go not in the way of evil men.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Hear, ye children, the instruction of a father, and attend to know understanding.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eph. 6:4 (1\u20134).",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For I give you good doctrine, forsake ye not my law.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For I was my father's son, tender and only beloved in the sight of my mother.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He taught me also, and said unto me, Let thine heart retain my words: keep my commandments, and live.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Get wisdom, get understanding: forget it not; neither decline from the words of my mouth.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 815
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Forsake her not, and she shall preserve thee: love her, and she shall keep thee.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wisdom is the principal thing; therefore get wisdom: and with all thy getting get understanding.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wisdom.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Learn; Problem-Solving; Understanding.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Exalt her, and she shall promote thee: she shall bring thee to honour, when thou dost embrace her.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "She shall give to thine head an ornament of grace: a crown of glory shall she deliver to thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Beauty.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Hear, O my son, and receive my sayings; and the years of thy life shall be many.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 20:12.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I have taught thee in the way of wisdom; I have led thee in right paths.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Leadership.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When thou goest, thy steps shall not be straitened; and when thou runnest, thou shalt not stumble.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0distressed, hampered.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 89:20 (19\u201320).",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Take fast hold of instruction; let her not go: keep her; for she is thy life.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 15:24 (23\u201324).",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Education.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Enter not into the path of the wicked, and go not in the way of evil men.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 12:17 (16\u201318).",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Avoid it, pass not by it, turn from it, and pass away.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For they sleep not, except they have done mischief; and their sleep is taken away, unless they cause some to fall.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 105
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For they eat the bread of wickedness, and drink the wine of violence.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But the path of the just is as the shining light, that shineth more and more unto the perfect day.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 31:18 (17\u201321).",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Example; Light [noun].",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Discernment, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The way of the wicked is as darkness: they know not at what they stumble.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Darkness, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "My son, attend to my words; incline thine ear unto my sayings.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let them not depart from thine eyes; keep them in the midst of thine heart.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 4:25; Morm. 8:15; D&C 82:19.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 2:1.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For they are life unto those that find them, and health to all their flesh.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 19:17.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Keep thy heart with all diligence; for out of it are the issues of life.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Put away from thee a froward mouth, and perverse lips put far from thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0perverse. D&C 50:33 (32\u201333); 84:73; 105:24.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let thine eyes look right on, and let thine eyelids look straight before thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 4:21.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Ponder the path of thy feet, and let all thy ways be established.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Meditation.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Turn not to the right hand nor to the left: remove thy foot from evil.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}